Requirements (versions used in testing in parentheses):

1. Apache (2.2.26)

2. PHP 5.4 or later (5.4.30)

3. MySQL (5.6.21)


Installation

1. Download files on to server such that index.php is in or in a directory below the document root

2. Set values in Config.php accordingly.

(i) rootpath equals path to directory containing index.php relative to document root e.g. for /my/document/root/my/path/public/index.php, set as '/my/path/public'. If index.php is in the document root, set as ''

(ii) baseurl: append rootpath to 'http://myserver.com'

3. Import db.sql into database specified in Config.php e.g mysql -u root -p dbname < db.sql 


Features

-- TinyMCE WYSWIYG HTML editor

-- MathJax and google-code-prettify enabled

-- organise texts into categories, sub-categories, sub-sub-categories, etc.
